< text>
We called and the locksmith showed up in less than an hour to attempt to open our Sentry safe. The safe had some mechanical and electronic issues but the locksmith was tenacious and finally got the defective unit open.
Despite numerous strategies being tried, the safe would not cooperate and ultimately the technician used heavy tools to open the unit but he knew where to attack so our closet near the safe was not destroyed.
The service was great and the price was reasonable considering the amount of effort expended on opening this horrible Sentry product. If you cannot get your defective Sentry safe open, call Lusky.<//text>

<Pics>None< /Pics>< review>
It's classic FilipinX food and a comfort for generations far away from home AND bring your own insulin. Last time mom had the fresh lumpia and the wrapper was tender and fresh. Vegetarian options were (expectedly) limited but the ensaymadas are exactly what we were expecting. This time we only had time to run in and out. Service at the bakery counter is quick and the pandesal were, just as the ensaymadas were, a perfect recreation of warm memories. Mom says the mungo hopia were also on point, I couldn't tell you I hate mung beans. If you have a minute and a sweet tooth swing in, you will not be disappointed!<//review>

<user>118424980504842771643<//user><name>Amy AwakeandAlive</name>< Time>
1551859775139<//Time>
< rate>
4<//rate>
< Review>
Located on Top of the Hill next to Auto Zone in Daly City, Goldilocks serves turo-turo (point to what you b want) style. Their bakery boasta of many cakes for special occasions and there are pre-packaged delicacies you can grab to go as well.

If you haven't tried Filipino Food yet, try these guys!

Not only does the location have a clean eating area, the servers also understand the logic of cleanliness as seen in the way they handle your food.

Parking is free on site and it's an easy jump on the 280 freeway from there!

my favorite: UKOY

Thanks for reading my review!
Stay awake and alive.<//Review>

<Rate>2< /Rate>< Text>
I have been coming to this store since i was 6 years old and i am now 20. I have seen this store transition from owner to owner and the change in the layout through the years. I have even seen when they had a butcher and sold poultry and beef. Over this period of time i have slowly seen this store change into somthing completly diffrent from what i remember as a child and now it is like an ordinary dollar store. There is nothing that makes its stand out. It mainly caters to the locals who buy their daily needed items. I would have gave it more stars but it simply isnt a very good dollar store nor does it stay true to its price point.< /Text>

<user>102899167442218498009</user><date>1469833994388<//date>< Review>
DON'T take your iphone 6 plus (or any phone) in here to be repaired. The screen he installed was faulty and didn't work properly, it costs more than the apple store to replace the screen ($135 compared to $129), and the overall store experience is very poor (smells like weed, dog running around, door locked and no one there during normal store hours, repair times much longer than he tells you).

I took my phone, iphone 6 plus, to smartphone repair to have my cracked screen replaced. It cost $135 and took about an hour. However, the newly installed screen consistently malfunction, so I took it back. He replaced my screen, but the problem persisted. He told me it was my motherboard.
So, I took my phone into an apple store to have it looked at. The genius there told me that my phone hardware looked perfectly fine, but the screen from smartphone repair was low-quality, had faulty connectors, and was the cause of the persistent malfunction. Since I had a 3rd party work on my phone, it voided my warranty. My options were to try another 3rd party screen replacement or trade in my phone. I  chose to trade in my phone.
I started out with a cracked screen, but fully functioning phone, and ended up having to replace it because of malfunctioning screen and voided warranty.

At the apple store, I learned its CHEAPER to get your screen repaired at the apple store than at smartphone repair, 135 compared to 129.

So, if your considering getting your iphone repaired here, DON'T. Go to the apple store. Its CHEAPER, EASIER, takes less time, won't void the warranty on your phone, and they use higher quality screens.< /Review>

I only rate it 1 star because that's the lowest the ratings go.  This is one of the shadiest businesses I've been to and experienced.  I never write reviews for anything, ever.  But I had to create an account so that I can describe the horrendous experience I had at Smartphone Repair.

After waiting 30 minutes he cracks the replacement screen while snapping it in place and he does not have anymore screens in stock so he tells me that I have to go phone-less for the next day.

I go back the next day to pick up my phone and the home button does not work.  He has to open the phone back up to connect the wiring for the home button but he stripped the screw as he was working on it and can't get the phone open.  He then proceeds to drill into the screw head damaging the bottom of the phone in the process.  He opens the phone, makes the connection on the home button, then returns the phone back to me minus the screw that was damaged.  He does not have a replacement for the screw that he stripped.  He then asks for the full price.

He sees that I'm upset then claims that the new screen looks "beautiful" then tells me that it was my fault because I brought in a phone with stripped screws then starts getting very defensive.  This literally leads to a heated argument where he does not return the phone back to me and will not issue me a receipt (I had already given him the cash by this point).  Honestly, all I wanted to do is get out of there.

This was one of the shadiest guys I've ever had to deal with.  You may not have as bad as an experience that I had, but I would not want anyone to risk going through what I did.  I would rather buy a new iphone at full price then deal with sleazy business guys like this.<//Review>

<user>100879742814667051848<//user><username>Kassandra Jones<//username><Date>1600493706965<//Date>< Rating>
5<//Rating>
< Review>
Had an amazing night, was greeted at least four times just on the way to our table. Their process is a little different from normal restaurants so we were patiently taught how they work and before we knew it, we were being offered selections from vegetables to salads to filet mignon to lamb to chicken to so many different varieties you couldn't imagine. It's almost literally a reverse buffet, and then to top it all off the tres leche cake was oh my God so gloriously delicious. Reasonable price for all you can eat filet mignon, I swear, they were offering us helpings so fast that before we could stop or knew what was happening we were so stuffed we could hardly breathe. Would recommend a hundred times over, exceptional service, food and prices.< /Review>

<rating>1</rating>< Text>
I've been to several Brazilian Steak houses.. this one was by far the worst.

During covid, the salad bar isn't open for self-serve which makes sense, but then there is no one coming around with salad bar choices even though it's still offered on the menu... so if you dont want to eat meat you basically don't eat. We had 3 people in our group do the salad bar option, so this was terrible for them. Then, at the end of the meal, the staff claimed those people ate meat from other people's plates, which they did not, they dont eat meat, they only came to a Brazilian steak house to support the birthday we were attending. The restaurant tried to charge them over $60.00 each when all they ate was maybe 3 pieces of asparagus and a piece  of lettuce... it was an extremely uncomfortable experience. The entire time it felt like a trap and money hustling scheme.

The meat was fine, nothing to write home about when compared to other Brazilian steak houses.

Will not be recommending to friends who visit the area.< /Text>

< Review>
Wow!  I must start by saying I am NOT much of a meat person....opted for the amazing salad bar.
WELL worth it!
My husband and son had the full meat course.  Loved it!
The food was incredible!
Cocktails were perfect!(I had the mojito).
Most amazing was the service!
My son dropped his fork and before he had time to reclaim it, a lovely gentlemen brought him a replacement.  Our waters were never below half full....

I have never witnessed such impeccable service.  Ever.  From our waiter to the gentlemen bringing the meat....This place has definitely invested and fully executed a true customer service experience.  I have worked in the hospitality industry all my life and have NEVER experienced such service!
Props to the owners, managers, for the dedication to expectations.  To the entire team that assisted us(must have been at least 8 individuals working with our table throughout the evening)were lovely human beings!
I WILL be back!
My only fear is they have set the bar too high...not sure I won't compare our service moving forward to this amazing place
Kudos to a wonderful group of people!<//Review>

< user_name>
Suzette C.<//user_name>
< date>
1559326572878</date>
< rate>
5<//rate>
<review>In this day and age there are a tremendous amount of options for one to dine at. I have barely tried all of the world's cuisine, but I intend to one bite at a time. A Brazilian steakhouse happens to be one of them!

On A Saturday evening we had reservations for 6:00 pm.  By then the parking lot was completely full and we had to use Napa Winery Inn's lot next door. No big deal. We were politely greeted and waited a few minutes before being seated.

For attire you can get away with everyday wear. Not everyone followed this, but to my surprise there were a lot of guests dressed casually. I felt a little overdressed from everyone. Nonetheless a lot of the staff had smiles no matter who they were serving.

Our waitress Tahis for the evening was just wonderful from beginning to end. Maybe I just haven't been to many restaurants with excellent service. It was the little things she did on her own like asking if we wanted fresh mashed potatoes or bananas throughout our meal. Without asking she gave us new plates instead of using the same one. Her demeanor was genuinely hospitable and very attentive. She alone gets five stars!

Buffet ($59.95)-

They do have a gourmet salad bar that had a variety of items including; vegetables, cured meats, cheeses, sushi, deviled eggs, bacon, and more. There were also a few selections of hot soups. We were also given cheese bread and mashed potatoes at our table.  I will admit, nothing was really memorable compared to the meats we had. Although, I would like to try the soups next time though.

From a handful of mixed reviews I was hesitant to how our experience would be with the all you can eat meats. On a whole we happily devoured each delicious mouthful of seasoned well meat. The bottom sirloin steak was the only tidbit that I thought was unpleasantly overcooked. Sidenote, the simple caramelized bananas went perfect with the meat. The sweet and savory hit the spot!

For the amount you pay per person it is expensive and probably not the best place to bring children unless they really have an appetite. I would suggest eating your money's worth before calling it quits! Our lovely dining experience was exactly what we needed to celebrate our 11 year anniversary. My Love is already set on having our anniversary dinner there again!< /review>< pics>

<rate>5<//rate>< Text>
The best way to put it is that their price is very steep and I still can't complain. I wouldn't go there every day because I would go broke, but when I want my wife to know she's worth it this place passes with flying colors. It's particularly special for steak lovers (my wife) but I can't get enough of their sausage and lamb. I'm not a steak lover but they still definitely make close to or possibly the best steak I've ever had and my wife agrees. I don't mind paying their steep price on occasion because when it's this good I want to be a part of making sure it doesn't go away. Tip: if you show up here, show up hungry--it's all you can eat and it's so good I often regret not being hungrier.< /Text>

< Review>
We had our mother's day lunch/dinner here and it was well worth the price. The servers have been really helpful on how to go on with getting our fill and the gauchos that served the food have been quick to response. There is about 17 types of Brazilian BBQ that you can pick from and we only went through about 6 or 7. Their lamb chops are great, the flavor or the rosemary combined well with the flavor of the meat. The pork was tender and juicy not dry at all, and the flavor of spices that were used enchances the flavor of the pork just right and their beef was just how I like it (medium to medium rare). I liked how the beef was seasoned just right and how there are some charred parts that made me crave for more. The dessert complimented the BBQ by toning down the experience to end the meal perfectly. My wife, my sister, my daughter and I enjoyed it very much. Next time we will bring our appetite and I may be able to go through all 17 choices in their menu. Thank you for the experience.< /Review>

< Text>
Excellent Atmosphere...Excellent Food.

One Issue...We visited for a 2pm lunch on a Sunday.  The restaurant wasn't busy at all, but we constantly felt rushed. We drove 2 hours from northern Lake County to visit this restaurant and the whole visit was done in 38 minutes.  When you spend $200 for a meal, you expect to enjoy it and not feel rushed.  There was a constant flow of staff coming to the table to offer food, replace plates, fill water glasses, etc. etc. regardless of our little table cards flipped to the red side. I think its fair to say that 5 minutes never passed without someone visiting the table.

If we make it back to the restaurant, we hope to not feel so rushed.< /Text>

< Text>

< Review>
Expensive but well worth it!
The entire experience and how professional the service is was beyond imagine. We had a hard time finishing our water and drinks cause they were Soo prompt with their service.
You get a small card that lays on the table and you flip it to is green side and prepare for the onslaught of delicious cuts of beef.
This is how great the service is.
They checked my Girl friends ID card to make sure she was of age to consume alcohol.
And when we asked for our check they have us a molten lava cake and some well wishes.
Not once did we mention it was her birthday.
I work in customer service and I would have never thought about something like that.
A+ service.
There's a reason why this place is well known.
The over all experience was well worth the price and I will be coming here for every special occasion< /Review>

<review>If you absolutely love meat then this is the place to go! Came here on a Friday night - All of the meat that was served was delicious to the last bite! The steak was like butter when cut. Didn't struggle with the knife at all. They come around with different types of meat,17 different types of meat. (rib eye, sirloin, prime rib, and MORE) ask how would you like your meat and they cut the perfect piece for you. Every bite had the right seasoning, char, fat and juiciness. I enjoyed this experience with a group of friends who all thought the same thing.

Dessert - I had a strawberry creme and my bf had the molten cake. Both were scrumptious and I didn't know which one I liked better. How about ordering BOTH again, just to finalize my decision.

The salad bar had an immense selection of cheese! There was smoked salmon, fresh veggies, salami, sushi, bread and so much more than I was to excited to remember everything there.

The inside has a fine romantic dining ambiance feel which made it more enjoyable. Location of the restaurant is really easy to get too, right off the highway! I normally am one to take photos of my food and where I am and post it on every social media I have but I was so impressed by this place that I didn't even want to ruin the setting of how beautiful it was.

I am going to have to take my mom here and the rest of my family to experience this amazing place.<//review><Pics>None<//Pics>< Resp>

<review>Great selection of food. Impeccable staff!
You sit down for drinks, then to a salad bar (not much salad, mostly cheeses, deli meat, sun dried tomatoes, olive dishes, sushi, veggie dishes, and 2 bowls of salad).
Upon arrival to your table, you are greated with an onslaught of various meat (chicken pork, salmon, and lamb). You may pass or accept any meat (rare, medium or done, and in between). There's a red and green card to let them know if you want more meat or if you are enjoying the food and don't want another slice at that time. There's one server for a table with 3-4 others serving the meat. It is a we'll trained and choreographed meal.
Once done with the main course, there's dessert too.
Overall great experience, clean restaurant, and gregarious staff.< /review><Pictures>None</Pictures><Rating>5< /Rating><date>1512709426027< /date><Gmap_id>0x8085072c051576f1:0xef004a4a10bf4322<//Gmap_id>< UserId.>

Spent Valentine's Day with my fiance here. From the bread, to the amazing buffet-style salad bar, and table-side cuts of sirloin, lamb chops, ribeye, pork sausage, and may other meats. < rate>

<time>1522118892845< /time>< Text>
The steak here was some of the best I've ever had in my life. There's quite a large selection of meats to choose from, most of which are beef. Each meat item served has its own flavor and texture, which keeps the experience fresh as you try the different items. There's also a salad bar (which has a few other items such as bread, not just salad) that you can use if you need a break from meat during your meal. The atmosphere and service is also great. Just make sure you're hungry before you come, as it's all-you-can-eat and you'll want to get your money's worth, as it's very expensive. For this reason, it's a place that's best visited for special occasions.</Text>

< text>
The food is amazing, only beaten by the fantastic service. I left absolutely stuffed to the gills, and still a little disappointed I wasn't able to try everything. This is easily one of my favorite dinner spots in Napa now.

<date>1530073957840< /date><rating>4< /rating>< Review>
Lots of great meat! Good beer on draft, I had a great dark beer that went well with my dinner.
Started with the salad & cheese bar. There were four cheeses & at least five cold meats. Salad condiments included hart of palm, sushi, asparagus & many other high end goodys.
Don't overlook the hot rolls! I don't know how they are made, but they are great. Mashed cheese potatoes and fried bananas are the sides I was served.
I focused mostly on beef, with a spicy top round & the flay menon being my favorites.
Also had a Brazilian flan to finish.
Over all great food, at a fair but high end price.</Review>

<UserId.>105192303350871898415<//UserId.><username>Claire Silver< /username>< date>
1519100195087< /date>
< rating>
4< /rating>
< text>
Always a great experience. Servers are kind, always in a great mood and super accommodating. The meat preparations are en point. All you can eat can be great after a day of tasting heavy wines of Napa.

Don't go if you are looking for a quiet, uninterrupted meal. The nature of this is restaurant is interactive and you should be ready for a steady flow of meat sabers until the check comes. It's a lot of fun if you are ready for a familiar family style dinner and the meat comma that follows.

Kid friendly, if your kids like meat. Loud enough to get away with minor tantrums and servers are understanding- bringing kids cups and removing sharp knives.

Can generally sneak in without a resy, but not always.  Definitely worth a try at least once for the fun of it.</text>

< Text>
Food was really good! A bit pricey, but then again it is Napa... anywhere you go other than Denny's and fast food is going to be expensive! Food was fantastic, it is an all you can eat place, and they even have cards on the tables for the meat that says yes please on one side,and no thank you on the other! There is a bar with food that you can eat, but save your appetites, because there are guys that come around with 14 different cuts of meat for you to eat! It really is a cool experience! <pics>None< /pics><resp>None< /resp><GmapID>0x8085072c051576f1:0xef004a4a10bf4322<//GmapID><user_name>Mr G< /user_name>< review>
ENDLESS (!!) cuts of meat are juicy and delicious, and this place has just enough atmosphere to prove they are serious about the business, without being too good for my kind (nice pair of jeans and collared shirt is ok).  Noise level is befitting of a place full of hungry, excited customers (you may not be able to hear conversation a few seats away). Buffet with a few dozen selections of hors d'oeuvres is complementary, as is a small selection of desserts.  Drinks and other desserts can be purchased in addition.  Be prepared to spend over $75 per person, knowing that in return you will leave with a greater appreciation of the fullness of life.</review>

Ok, so I don't leave reviews ever, and I mean ever! But to put it simply this place has delivered for me twice in my life. The first time being my 3rd date with the woman I ended up marrying, the 2nd time being my wedding reception. My wife an her family are from Brazil and I wanted to make sure they felt at home. < Review>
Went here on Saturday and enjoyed excellent, friendly service and a great meal. We did feel a bit rushed though. Atmosphere is noisy and decor is a bit uninspired. Drinks were expensive even for Napa. Meat selection was not as extensive as some Brazilian BBQs I've been to, but everything was well prepared and full of flavor. Worth the visit and will go back.<//Review>

105846273630052913765< /userid>
< Name>
Robert Blunt</Name>
< time>
1511898578888< /time>
< rate>
5</rate>
< text>
I visited the restaurant with my wife for my birthday dinner over the Thanksgiving holiday weekend.

We were greeted at our table by our waiter JJ. He is Brazilian and was fun to talk with. He gave us the lowdown on how the restaurant worked since it was our first time in a Brazilian steakhouse.

We started at the salad bar which was much more then that. Smoked salmon, vegetables, sushi, cheese and much more. Be careful not to eat much to save room for the main course.

We also had Pao de Queijo which is Brazilian cheese bread. So good but don't fill up.

We were then told to turn over these cards at our table when we were ready to eat. They had red on one side and green in the other for obvious reasons.

We went green and waiter after waiter came by our table to slice of tender goodness of bottom Sirloin, top sirloin, braised rib, lamb chops, filet minion with and without bacon. On and on everything was delicious. Salmon, sausages, ribs all tender and mouth watering. We had to turn over the red card a few times.

After dinner JJ brought out a birthday chocolate molton desert for my wife and I to share. Outstanding.

Overall experience great. Food awesome. You will not leave hungry. On the pricey side but worth it.< /text>

< userid>
116790674653672656690<//userid>
< username>
AM Young</username>
<Time>1504711845009</Time><Rating>5< /Rating>< review>
Wow. Too amazing for words yet I will attempt to convey the sheer pleasure as well as satisfaction of experience we had today.
My husband and I arrived early for dinner service ( we left home early not knowing that the restaurant was so easily located right off the freeway with very clear signs) which began promptly at 5pm.
Although we were early by about 15 min we were greeted most generally by the hostess who seated us at a table by the bar with not one but three menus to order a multitude of dishes and cocktails to pass the time.
I went to wash my hands and found that the bathroom was not simply clean but had a scent of flowers. It was similar to a fresh spring bouquet.
I was again amazed by the beautiful fountain that greeted me at the sink. Quite unique in that it resembled an antique wine pump. Truly amazing. I had to ask my husband to "go and wash your hands" because I knew I couldn't describe it and give it the awe inspiring description it deserved.
He loved the attention to detail as well (I also told him I would love that to be an addition to our bathroom remodel).
The restaurant is simply beautiful. Upscale, classy yet without pretense.
A fancy gala or (as we were in) jeans and shorts are all completely comfortable.
As we were greeted and attended to by many staff, one of which took our drink order promptly as well as bringing soft, warm, egg shaped and sized bread in a basket that brought back memories of my mother's home made bread with home made yeast, full of love and flavor. Delicately crispy crust with a warm and tender inside...Mmmmm.
Before I knew it we were being seated. She gave us our choice. Nice touch.
We started at the ample salad bar. Not wanting to fill up on salad as this was our first experience at an all you can eat Brazilian bbq, I limited my choices to the asparagus, cheeses, chicken salad, brown bread and butter. Too delicious!
Then the meats begin to come.
The entire staff is welcoming. Our server kindly explaining the way it all works and how to get more from the menu. The laughter, the quality, the atmosphere, the attention to detail. Every detail. Even when I wanted to save the rack of lamb bones for our dogs (we have three), it was not simply accommodated but done without hesitation.
I ate more than I've ever managed. Ribeye, rack of lamb, sirloin, salmon, filet and more. Most was cooked to perfection. The salmon was dry but saved by a bit of lemon and the sweet yet tart sauce served with it. The end pieces of sirloin my husband had were a bit tough but only in comparison to the melt in your mouth meats the proceeded it.
When one of the meat entrees was not in circulation, I had but to ask and it was moments later on my plate.
I have not had such a euphoric dining experience in over 20 years.
Thank you, thank you, thank you!!!
There are many places with 5 star or close to 5 star ratings. But  we have been disappointed by most. On the other hand... YOU all, truly deserve it! We will be dining again and again. Most importantly we will be singing your praises and bring others to enjoy the pleasure of dining with you!
Thank you for a world class experience at Galpao Goucho in Napa!<//review>
